goals.question: What is the trend of disasters over the years?
goals.visualization: line chart of Year vs count
goals.rationale: This visualization will help to understand if the number of disasters has increased or decreased over the years.

goals.question: What is the distribution of deaths caused by disasters?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help to understand the range of deaths caused by disasters and the frequency of their occurrence.

goals.question: Which entity has the highest number of disasters?
goals.visualization: bar chart of Entity vs count

goals.question: What is the relationship between the number of disasters and deaths?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of count vs Deaths
goals.rationale: This visualization will help to understand if there is a correlation between the number of disasters and deaths caused by them.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of disasters over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Deaths'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Deaths'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Deaths', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Deaths'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Deaths'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of deaths caused by disasters?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = data['count'].astype(int)
    data = data.groupby('Entity')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x="Entity", y="count", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.set(xlabel='Entity', ylabel='Count')
    ax.axhline(y=data['count'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max Count: {:.2f}'.format(data['count'].max()))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Entity'] = data['Entity'].astype('category')
    entity_counts = data['Entity'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(entity_counts, labels=entity_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the most common type of disaster?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
